reviews.review_text:
10-25-85 Sportatorium The Source, and Notes could have been clearer:  Set 1 is a FOB AUD, and I'd give it one star. It's unbalanced: too much cymbals and other high-end sounds.,it also has drop outs, clicks, and the levels get turned up too high initially.  I couldn't listen to it.

Set2 is a SBD, and I'd give it a 5 for quality, but the Dew has quriky tempo and lacks Umph.  I give the performance a 3.

erik65 You rushed your vote! This SBD gave me a flashback! Uncle Charlie strikes again! The"DEAL" opener is an AUD. recording, the rest of the show is a SUPER SOUNDING SBD!! erik64 or 65, who ever you are, you didn"t listen to the whole 1st set! I got a flashback buzz listening to this show, and I wasn't even there! Some sloppiness from the band at times, but so what! They rock and this recording rocks! Great mid-80's sound! Thank you Mr.Charlie!! Thanks for the heads up Burnt Rich!!!

Dude, its a 2nd set Dew opener. How often did that happen. 1st set is "backward" too, with a  Deal opener.
 Its a long 2-lane road to the sportatorium.Stuck in bad traffic after workin the delivery van, my brother who was not a deadhead told me to go on and walk if I wanted to catch the beginning of the show, and we would meet at the set break. I looked and looked until the boys came back on stage and dropped into the Dew....
After the show my bro was out in front of the show drunk assed in the van--He went to the DOG TRACK!
Pushing It The boys were in a HUGE rush on this show...........Slow Down!  Drugs are still going to be there fellas...hated the "80's  Thank;s Charlie!!!!

never gonna miss us.. So you came for the 1st set Deal opener hope you rode it thru to the Let It Grow closer,
So you come for the 2nd set Morning Dew opener hope you made it thru to the Eyes>Drums>Space>Miracle.
1985 was the year for me (touring 84>93)
Give me a rocket charged freight train --1985
For This Year --a 2nd tier sugary goodness.           Strong 4 bolts!
Old Sportatorium-nuff said.
One of those rare nights in the mid 80's 
when Garcia has more to offer vocally than Weir.
and what a pretty EYES OF THE WORLD.
Deal Deal is not my favorite anyway. I leave it off my recordings.
